{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_non_black_grey_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    non_black_grey_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] not in [black, grey]:\n                non_black_grey_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return non_black_grey_pixels\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    p = find_non_black_grey_pixels(input_grid)\n    a = find_covering_area(input_grid, p)\n    out = find_grey_centered_3x3_area(a, input_grid)\n    return out\ndef find_covering_area(input_grid: np.ndarray, p: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> Tuple[int, int, int, int]:\n    min_i, min_j = input_grid.shape\n    max_i = max_j = 0\n    for i, j in p:\n        min_i = min(min_i, i)\n        max_i = max(max_i, i)\n        min_j = min(min_j, j)\n        max_j = max(max_j, j)\n    return (min_i, max_i+1, min_j, max_j+1)\ndef find_grey_centered_3x3_area(a: Tuple[int, int, int, int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Find the grey pixel out of area a, let it be the center pixel, copy the 3x3 area a in the new 3x3 area in the input_grid whose center is the grey pixel\n    \n    Args:\n    a: A tuple of integers representing the covering area of the non-black and non-grey pixels in the input grid. The tuple contains four values: the minimum row index, the maximum row index plus one, the minimum column index, and the maximum column index plus one.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid. The array contains integers representing the color of each pixel in the grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid. The array contains integers representing the color of each pixel in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    center_pixel = None\n    for i in range(a[0], a[1]):\n        for j in range(a[2], a[3]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == grey:\n                center_pixel = (i, j)\n                break\n        if center_pixel:\n            break\n    out = np.zeros((3, 3), dtype=int)\n    for i in range(center_pixel[0] - 1, center_pixel[0] + 2):\n        for j in range(center_pixel[1] - 1, center_pixel[1] + 2):\n            if i >= a[0] and i < a[1] and (j >= a[2]) and (j < a[3]):\n                out[i - center_pixel[0] + 1][j - center_pixel[1] + 1] = input_grid[i][j]\n    return out", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    p = `find all not black and not grey pixels`(input_grid)\n    a = `find the 3x3 area in the input_grid which could cover all pixels in p`(input_grid, p)\n    out = `find the grey pixel, let it be the center pixel, copy the 3x3 area a`(a, input_grid)\n    return out", "gpt_code": "def find_non_black_grey_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    non_black_grey_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] not in [black, grey]:\n                non_black_grey_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return non_black_grey_pixels\ndef find_covering_area(input_grid: np.ndarray, p: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> Tuple[int, int, int, int]:\n    min_i, min_j = input_grid.shape\n    max_i = max_j = 0\n    for i, j in p:\n        min_i = min(min_i, i)\n        max_i = max(max_i, i)\n        min_j = min(min_j, j)\n        max_j = max(max_j, j)\n    return (min_i, max_i+1, min_j, max_j+1)\ndef find_grey_centered_3x3_area(a: Tuple[int, int, int, int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Find the grey pixel out of area a, let it be the center pixel, copy the 3x3 area a in the new 3x3 area in the input_grid whose center is the grey pixel\n    \n    Args:\n    a: A tuple of integers representing the covering area of the non-black and non-grey pixels in the input grid. The tuple contains four values: the minimum row index, the maximum row index plus one, the minimum column index, and the maximum column index plus one.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid. The array contains integers representing the color of each pixel in the grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid. The array contains integers representing the color of each pixel in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    center_pixel = None\n    for i in range(a[0], a[1]):\n        for j in range(a[2], a[3]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == grey:\n                center_pixel = (i, j)\n                break\n        if center_pixel:\n            break\n    out = np.zeros((3, 3), dtype=int)\n    for i in range(center_pixel[0] - 1, center_pixel[0] + 2):\n        for j in range(center_pixel[1] - 1, center_pixel[1] + 2):\n            if i >= a[0] and i < a[1] and (j >= a[2]) and (j < a[3]):\n                out[i - center_pixel[0] + 1][j - center_pixel[1] + 1] = input_grid[i][j]\n    return out", "holes": {"find_non_black_grey_pixels": "find all not black and not grey pixels", "find_covering_area": "find the 3x3 area in the input_grid which could cover all pixels in p", "find_grey_centered_3x3_area": "Find the grey pixel out of area a, let it be the center pixel, copy the 3x3 area a in the new 3x3 area in the input_grid whose center is the grey pixel"}}
